06/04/2006
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- The World Bank, the European Commission and USAID pledged 56m euros on Wednesday (5 April) to help cover Kosovo's budget deficit in 2006 and 2007. The Serbian province has an annual budget of around 700m euros. The 2006 deficit is projected at 50m euros. 
In Athens, meanwhile, diplomats from the United States, Russia and six EU countries met to discuss the situation in Kosovo with counterparts from Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Macedonia, Moldova, Romania, Serbia-Montenegro and Turkey. UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen and UN deputy special envoy Albert Rohan also attended the closed-door talks. In a statement afterwards, participants expressed support for the reconciliation of ethnic communities and protection of minority rights in Kosovo. (AP, Tanjug, RTS, Pravda, KosovaLive - 05/04/06)
